textBox.richText: Poetry competition @ Catholic Christian? Homeschool, children 5-14, Taara is the accuracy judge, along with three of her colleagues from the Santa Clara review. “Parking behind Shrine” sign on the way here. comical “let’s find the right shrine to park next to” American suburbanism in a single message -Relgion Petroleum + Park They just recited all this Christian psycho-babble cults: they cray cray. Hmm Louis Carroll, interesting choice for Christians. “Sit back & enjoy this ... exxxxxcittttiiiinnnggggg Reeccccciittttinnng!” She’s so proud of herself. Everyone is forced to memorize the poem, must be a Christian thing, all about reciting, brainwashing. They are more focused on not messing up than the actual meaning behind the words.
